Question: Do you think it is ok for the government to read your emails for counter-terrorism purposes?
Answer:
No. I do not think it is ok for the government to read my emails for counter-terrorism purposes. First of all, citizens in America have a right to privacy, which I would think includes emails. Second of all, the government requires a legal document and some sort of proof that I am involved in illegql activities. That the government reads my emails to prevent any sort of counter-terrorism is, in my eyes, an invasion of my rights as an American.